  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "SEC1",
      "type": "heading",
      "title": "Resource Planning & Capacity Planning"
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Resource Planning assigns transportation resources such as trucks, trailers, containers, ships and aircraft to Freight Orders. Capacity Planning verifies whether these resources have sufficient weight, volume, space and availability to transport the assigned Freight Units efficiently."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC3",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "important",
      "title": "Key Concept",
      "content": "Capacity Planning answers the question: 'Can this resource transport the assigned shipment without violating capacity or scheduling constraints?'"
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC4",
      "type": "heading",
      "title": "Objectives of Resource Planning"
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC5",
      "type": "bullet-list",
      "items": [
        "Assign suitable vehicles",
        "Maximize resource utilization",
        "Prevent vehicle overloading",
        "Optimize transportation schedules",
        "Reduce empty trips",
        "Improve transportation efficiency"
      ]
    },
    {
