    },
    {
      "id": "SEC16",
      "type": "bullet-list",
      "items": [
        "Higher vehicle utilization",
        "Reduced transportation cost",
        "Better resource scheduling",
        "Improved delivery reliability",
        "Lower empty mileage",
        "Reduced manual planning"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC17",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "best-practice",
      "title": "Best Practice",
      "content": "Maintain accurate resource capacities, calendars and equipment details. Capacity planning is only effective when resource master data is complete and up to date."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC18",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "example",
      "title": "Real Project Example",
      "content": "A logistics company integrated GPS-enabled fleet data with SAP TM. Resource planning automatically assigned the nearest available truck, reducing empty travel distance by 18%."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC19",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "interview-tip",
      "title": "Interview Tip",
      "content": "A common interview question is: 'What happens if the selected vehicle exceeds its capacity?' SAP TM validates capacity constraints and either selects another resource or splits the shipment if required."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC20",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "warning",
      "title": "Common Mistake",
      "content": "Resource Planning is not only about assigning vehicles. It also considers driver availability, equipment compatibility, calendars and legal working time restrictions."
    },
    {
